      <title>[Letter], 1857 Nov. 11, Washington City [to the] Secretary of the Treasury / W[illia]m H. Thomas</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>This document is a letter from William H. Thomas, legal representative of the North Carolina Cherokees, dated November 11, 1857 to the acting Secretary of the Treasury regarding a number of treaties, acts, and resolutions specific to the payment of annuities to the eastern Cherokees. Thomas quotes from several of these legal documents in arguing for the appropriate payments due the North Carolina Cherokees and pointing out obvious discrepancies in the federal policies. This document was originally bound (as wtp080) with the following documents in the Southeastern Native American Documents Database: wtp081, wtp082, wtp083, wtp084.</abstract>
